      "date": "2012-12-27 05:10:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nLooks good.  Currently, opd_pre_status will not be zero immediately upon a reconnection but only after the initial OST_STATFS RPC or the orphan recovery RPC.  Thus, the obd_timeout expiration in osp_precreate_reserve() is not strictly long enough.  I guess this is tolerable?",
